		<geography>
			<locationOfOperationSupplyOrProduction location="CN">
				<descriptionOfRestrictions xml:lang="en">Environmental effects of China's solar photovoltaic industry during2011e2016: A life cycle assessment approach</descriptionOfRestrictions>
				<descriptionOfRestrictions xml:lang="zh">2011-2016年中国太阳能光伏产业生命周期环境影响评价</descriptionOfRestrictions>
			</locationOfOperationSupplyOrProduction>
		</geography>
		<technology>
			<technologyDescriptionAndIncludedProcesses xml:lang="en">Ingot breaker is used to slice the ingot</technologyDescriptionAndIncludedProcesses>
			<technologyDescriptionAndIncludedProcesses xml:lang="zh">钢锭破碎机是用来切割钢锭的</technologyDescriptionAndIncludedProcesses>
			<technologicalApplicability xml:lang="en">The described industrial process involves slicing ingots of multi-crystalline silicon (multi-Si) to produce wafers for photovoltaic (PV) modules. Each PV module is part of a larger solar energy system, with a focus on a 1 kWp system that incorporates five individual 200 W modules, each composed of 54 multi-Si cells. These cells have dimensions of 156 x 156 mm2 and possess an efficiency of 16%. The process is therefore crucial for the manufacturing of PV panels, which are used in the solar power industry to capture and convert solar energy into electricity.</technologicalApplicability>
			<technologicalApplicability xml:lang="zh">上述工业过程包括切割多晶硅锭以生产光伏模块用的晶圆。每个光伏模块是更大的太阳能系统的一部分，重点是一个包括五个各自由54个多晶硅电池组成的200 W模块的1 kWp系统。这些电池的尺寸为156 x 156 mm2，效率为16%。因此，该过程是制造太阳能电池板的关键步骤，太阳能电池板在太阳能电力行业中用于捕获和转换太阳能为电能。</technologicalApplicability>
			<referenceToTechnologyFlowDiagrammOrPicture type="source data set" refObjectId="12a1e0b7-2f33-c1ae-b57b-afe1edf94591" uri="../sources/12a1e0b7-2f33-c1ae-b57b-afe1edf94591.xml">
				<common:shortDescription xml:lang="en">WVsFbvbstoAQ0Bxrb4KcnEX7nCf.png</common:shortDescription>
			</referenceToTechnologyFlowDiagrammOrPicture>
		</technology>
	</processInformation>
